Uses of Package
interfaces.dao

Packages that use interfaces.dao
Package
Description
dao
The dao package contains Data Access Object (DAO) classes responsible for interacting with the underlying data storage and performing CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations.
services
The services package contains classes that provide various services and functionalities for the SC2002_CAMs application.
views
The views package contains classes that provide various output for the SC2002_CAMs application.
  • Classes in interfaces.dao used by dao
    Class
    Description
    CampDao
    The CampDao interface defines methods for accessing and manipulating camp-related data in the CAMs system.
    CommitteeMemberDao
    The CommitteeMemberDao interface defines methods for accessing and manipulating committee members-related data in the CAMs system.
    CurrentUserDao
    The CurrentUserDao interface defines methods for accessing and manipulating the current user information in the CAMs system.
    StaffDao
    The StaffDao interface defines methods for accessing and manipulating staff information in the CAMs system.
    StudentDao
    The StudentDao interface defines methods for accessing and manipulating student information in the CAMs system.
